olive oil
1 Brown Onion
1 potato
1 carrot
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
2 packet chicken breast
20 g butter
1 tsp honey
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 bag Corn Chips
1 packet sour cream
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend
1 packet BBQ sauce

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Slice onion into wedges. Cut potato and carrot into bite-sized chunks.

• Place onion, potato and carrot on a lined oven tray. Sprinkle with garlic & herb seasoning and drizzle with olive oil.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Help toss the veggies and seasoning.

• Meanwhile, cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.
• When veggies have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken in batches, tossing occasionally, until browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Return all chicken to the pan, then add All-American spice blend and the butter and cook, tossing, until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove pan from the heat, then add BBQ sauce and the honey. Toss chicken to coat.

• When veggies are done, add baby spinach leaves to the tray and toss to combine.
• Crush corn chips in their bag until roughly broken into pieces.
• Divide roast veggie toss between bowls. Top with BBQ sauce-glazed chicken and crushed corn chips.
• Dollop with sour cream to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Join the fun and help crush the corn chips!